  "local_port": 60266,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My car back glass has been broken, how can I claim United India insurance?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about the damage to your car. Filing an insurance claim with United India Insurance involves several steps. Here's a general guide to help you through the process:\n\n1. **Report the Incident Immediately**: \n   - As soon as you notice the damage, inform United India Insurance by calling their customer service helpline. You can find the number on your insurance policy documents or on the company's website.\n\n2. **Document the Damage**:\n   - Take clear photographs of the broken back glass and any other damage related to the incident. \n   - Make a note of the date, time, and location of the incident.\n\n3. **Filing a Claim**:\n   - Visit the nearest United India Insurance branch or use their online platform if available.\n   - Fill out the required claim form. Make sure that you provide accurate and detailed information about the incident and the damages.\n\n4. **Submit Necessary Documents**:\n   - Provide a copy of your insurance policy.\n   - Submit the filled claim form.\n   - Include photographs of the damage.\n   - In case of an accident, you may need an FIR (First Information Report) if required for the claim.\n   - Any other documents requested by the insurance company.\n\n5. **Inspection and Approval**:\n   - United India Insurance may send an inspector to evaluate the damage to your car.\n   - Once the inspection is complete, the insurance company will approve the claim if all the documents are in order and the damage is covered under your policy.\n\n6. **Repair Process**:\n   - Depending on the insurance company's policy, you can either go to their network garage for repairs or choose your own garage and get an estimate.\n   - Some policies may also cover direct cashless repair services.\n\n7. **Claim Settlement**:\n   - After the repair is completed, if it is cashless, the garage will settle the bill directly with the insurance company.\n   - If you paid for the repairs, submit the bills to United India Insurance for reimbursement.\n   \nRemember to keep copies of all correspondence, forms, and receipts related to the claim for your records. For specific details related to your policy, it's best to contact United India Insurance directly or refer to your policy documentation.",
